      "description": "The Bill of Rights exists only as a scaffold. All identity-defining articles (I–VI) are placeholder text '[To be defined by human principal]'. This means the organism has no written Core Identity, Scope of Enterprise, Prohibited Activities, Human Authority Reservation, Amendment Protocol, or Interpretation Rules. The organism's fundamental nature and boundaries are constitutionally undefined.",
