      "why_constitutional": "The BoR is the supreme constitutional document that Arbiter (#190) uses to enforce the scope perimeter. Without its identity articles, the organism has no 'what it IS and must NEVER do' specification. Arbiter cannot gate actions, and Nomos (#200) cannot verify that actions conform to a core identity. While the recent goal-stream is empty (no immediate conflict), the constitutional void means any future goal could operate without identity constraints, effectively bypassing all constitutional protection.",
      "criticality": "critical",
      "urgency": "immediate",
      "impact": "The organism is currently operating with no constitutional identity boundaries. It could be directed to undertake any action without violating a defined BoR, because none exists. All governance architecture (Arbiter, Nomos, MSP) depends on the BoR for ultimate authority; its absence renders the entire constitutional order vacuous.",
      "priority_score": 1.0
    }
  ]
}

