      "criticality": "high",
      "urgency": "high",
      "impact": "operational",
      "description": "MSP Rules are the second compliance gate for Action Proposals. An empty Rules set means the system operates in default‑permissive mode with no relational guardrails. Even though Minder holds clear patterns of Leon’s expectations, there is no rule to translate these into binding commitments, making the DIO unable to guarantee it will respect the human principal’s attention preferences.",
      "relational_focus": "person-attention coverage, peer commitments (enforcement layer)"
