      "gap_id": "gap-msp-amendment-human-attention-encoding",
      "grounding": {
        "document": "MSP",
        "section": "Amendment Protocol",
        "reason": "The protocol defines a technical pipeline for rule changes triggered by PEMs and requires human approval via POST /amend/review. However, it provides no mechanism to capture or encode the human principal’s ongoing attention preferences (e.g., ‘ask before changing infrastructure’, ‘do not modify without explicit consent’). Person‑attention coverage relies entirely on the human noticing a PEM and reacting; there is no proactive relational commitment that the system will seek attention before acting, only after a block event."
