      "description": "The Amendment Protocol is reactive — it only engages when an AP is already blocked. It does not encode positive person‑attention obligations such as ‘always consult on category X’. Until rules are drafted, the human’s attention is treated as a fallback, not as a proactive relational commitment. This gap means that even if the BoR is later authored, the MSP may still lack the machinery to schedule person‑attention checks before rule‑governed actions.",
